[Gemini]: This case involves two queries pointing to unsafe deserialization in `jinja2/bccache.py`. The primary concern is the use of `pickle.load`, which can lead to remote code execution if an attacker can control the content of the file being deserialized. The bytecode cache (`bccache`) stores compiled template code on the filesystem. If an attacker can write to this cache directory, they can inject a malicious pickle payload.

I'll start by examining the code around the flagged lines to understand the file operations and how the data is loaded.

